Here is a script using HTML for the form and PHP for saving the text to a file.

You will need a web server with PHP installed to run this code.

**1. Create the HTML form (save as `index.html`)**

This file creates a simple form with a text area and a submit button. When submitted, it sends the data to `save_text.php`.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text Input Form</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Enter Your Text</h2>

    <form action="save_text.php" method="post">
        <label for="user_text">Your Text:</label><br>
        <textarea id="user_text" name="user_text" rows="10" cols="50" required></textarea>
        <br><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Save Text">
    </form>

</body>
</html>
```

**2. Create the PHP script to save the text (save as `save_text.php` in the same directory)**

This script receives the text from the form and appends it to a file named `saved_data.txt`.

```php
<?php
// Check if the form was submitted using the POST method
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {

    // Check if the 'user_text' field is not empty
    if (!empty($_POST['user_text'])) {

        // Get the text from the textarea
        $text_to_save = $_POST['user_text'];

        // Specify the file to save the text to
        $file_name = 'saved_data.txt';

        // Use file_put_contents to append the text to the file.
        // FILE_APPEND prevents overwriting the file's existing content.
        // Add a newline character "\n" to separate entries.
        // LOCK_EX prevents others from writing to the file at the same time.
        if (file_put_contents($file_name, $text_to_save . "\n", FILE_APPEND | LOCK_EX)) {
            echo "Text saved successfully!";
        } else {
            echo "Error: Unable to save the text.";
        }

    } else {
        echo "Error: Text field was empty.";
    }
} else {
    // If not a POST request, redirect back to the form or show an error
    echo "Invalid request method.";
}
?>
```

### How to Use:

1.  Save the two code blocks as `index.html` and `save_text.php` in the same folder on your web server.
2.  Open `index.html` in your web browser.
3.  Type text into the text area and click "Save Text".
4.  The text will be saved in a new file called `saved_data.txt` in the same directory. Each new submission will be added to a new line in that file.
